ðŸ”§ Installing Sass CSS on Linux
To use Sass in your project, follow the steps below to set up Node.js, NPM, and install Sass globally using npm.

âœ… Step 1: Install NVM (Node Version Manager)
NVM allows you to easily install and manage multiple versions of Node.js.

bash
Copy
Edit
# Download and install NVM
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.3/install.sh | bash

# Load NVM without restarting the shell
. "$HOME/.nvm/nvm.sh"
More info: https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm

âœ… Step 2: Install Node.js using NVM
bash
Copy
Edit
# Install the latest stable Node.js version (v22)
nvm install 22

# Verify Node.js version
node -v      # Should print: v22.17.0
nvm current  # Should print: v22.17.0

# Check npm version
npm -v       # Should print: 10.9.2
Node.js download link: https://nodejs.org

âœ… Step 3: Install Sass Globally
Once Node.js and npm are set up, install Sass using the following command:

bash
Copy
Edit
npm install -g sass
You can now use the sass command anywhere in your terminal.